The palette is an elegiac harmony of moonstone white, pale silver, rose‑gold, soft lavender, deep slate‑grey (for the Barren Lands), and the warm, golden‑white glow of Silvanna’s holy lance. The parchment is a soft, moon‑pale ivory. Light emanates from a single, full, mist‑veiled moon overhead, casting a diffuse, silver‑white glow that makes the spires and the Reflecting Pool gleam ethereally. The Beacon of the Southern Star adds a warm, vigilant counterpoint. A thick, volumetric ground‑fog of pale silver wash blankets the lower valley and the Pilgrim’s Path, adding an atmosphere of profound, beautiful mystery without obscuring a single stone of the castle.

